ailing what the backend folder needs.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n125 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:03.575Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Defining Backend Structure**\\n\\nI am currently working on the backend folder structure. I'm focusing on organizing the FastAPI app within `backend/app/`, breaking it down into `main.py` for the entry point and various sub-folders such as `core/` for configurations, `database/` for engine setup, `models/` for database schemas, `schemas/` for Pydantic validations, `api/` for sub-routers, `crud/` for utility functions, and `middleware/` for custom components. I'll also specify dependencies and Docker files.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n126 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:05.440Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Specifying Database Migrations**\\n\\nI'm now detailing database migrations. SQLite is the chosen local MVP solution; PostgreSQL will be considered for future production scaling, but SQLAlchemy/SQLModel abstractions simplify this transition. The models, mirroring `lib/mock-data-model.ts`, include User (id, email, hashed_password, full_name, role (enum), clearance_level, organization_id (optional), is_active, created_at, updated_at), ClientAccount / Organization (id, name, domain, status (enum), tier (enum), region, compliance_level, contact_name, contact_email, created_at, updated_at), and Project / Sandbox (id, name, desc, enclave_type)\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n127 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:06.785Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Defining Database Schema**\\n\\nI'm expanding the database schema, focusing on modeling critical data entities. I've defined schemas for AgentOperation and CognitivePipeline, AgentHealth, DocumentItem (SovereignVault), Invoice, SupportTicket, and SupportTicketReply, all essential for the application.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n128 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:08.627Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Detailing Security Components**\\n\\nI'm now detailing `GovernanceItem` and `ActivityLog` schemas for comprehensive data tracking. I'm focusing on attributes like IDs, names, standards, statuses, descriptions, timestamps, and foreign keys linking these items to client accounts and users.\\n\\nI am also developing a seed script, `backend/app/db/seed.py`, to populate the database with default users corresponding to various roles and match high-fidelity mock datasets. I'm focusing on secure password hashing with BCrypt and implementing idempotency checks to prevent duplicate data insertion. Additionally, I am designing authentication endpoints, specifically the `/api/auth/login` for user login, handling validation, JWT generation, and simulated MFA status.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n129 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:10.534Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Defining Authentication Endpoints**\\n\\nI'm now detailing authentication endpoints. I'm focusing on `/api/auth/mfa/verify` (POST) to validate TOTP codes for high-clearance access. I'm also planning `/api/auth/me` (GET) to return the user profile. I'm also designing `/api/auth/refresh` (POST) to handle secure token refreshing. I'll also add a `/api/auth/recover` (POST) for passphrase key recovery. I also need to make RBAC roles.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n130 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:12.236Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Implementing RBAC Roles**\\n\\nI'm now implementing RBAC roles within the FastAPI backend, mirroring defined roles exactly. I'm focusing on defining roles such as `gff_admin`, `gff_operator`, `finance_admin`, `support_agent`, and `viewer`. The backend will use `RBACDependency` or middleware to parse JWT claims for role and clearance, and enforce access control via dependency injection, such as `Depends(get_current_active_user_with_roles([\\\"gff_admin\\\", \\\"gff_operator\\\"]))`. I'm focusing on GET endpoints.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n131 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:13.362Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Designing Portal APIs**\\n\\nI am now focusing on designing the portal APIs. I'm focusing on defining endpoints for Agent cognitive pipeline configurations, secure document vault retrieval, billing ledger and invoices, and client support tickets, along with compliance monitoring.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n132 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:15.682Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Designing Admin APIs**\\n\\nI am now designing the admin APIs. Specifically, I am focusing on GET `/api/admin/billing`, which aggregates billing data across clients and triggers cryptographic seals. Also, I am designing GET `/api/admin/support` and POST `/api/admin/support/{id}/reply`, a global support ticket command center. Finally, GET `/api/admin/governance` is for system-wide audit logging and telemetry hash validation.\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n133 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:17.559Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Refining Authorization Strategy**\\n\\nI'm now detailing an effective authorization strategy for the frontend. I plan to use `middleware.ts` to implement redirects based on JWT cookies. I'll also develop client-side components to protect private routes with role and clearance checks. I'll use `jose` for lightweight JWT decoding, and the current mode will be based on an environment variable.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n134 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:19.395Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Implementing API Fetch Strategy**\\n\\nI'm now implementing the API fetch strategy. I'll use `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_MODE=\\\"api\\\"` so the `api-client` executes actual fetch queries to the FastAPI local server. I'll progressively convert pages, starting with login and session establishment, followed by passive lists (projects, operations), and finally handling write interactions (tickets, agent parameters). I'll also add local dev scripts.\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n135 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:21.348Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Finalizing Frontend Testing**\\n\\nI'm now focusing on frontend testing, specifically unit/integration tests for the API client. I'm verifying the fallback mechanism works correctly. I've also detailed the backend documentation, creating a `backend/README.md` that covers setup, API Swagger Docs, database schema, and dev tools. I've also covered data leakage as a key operational and security risk. Additionally, CORS and cookie misalignments are in the documentation. I need to handle MFA.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n136 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T09:29:23.500Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Addressing Session Integrity**\\n\\nI'm now addressing potential vulnerabilities related to user session integrity. I'm focusing on the implications of browser timer loops on TOTP code validation and the risk of user lockout due to clock desynchronization. I also need to ensure that the application handles Next.js Server-Side Rendering (SSR) versus Client-Side Rendering (CSR) session mismatches effectively, focusing on using secure cookies to avoid hydration errors that might cause issues. Further