{"ts":"2026-06-27T09:32:21.018Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"read_files","toolCallId":"5nt4fpjm","output":[{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/PHASE_4_LOGIN_ADMIN_CLIENT_PORTAL.md:1-150","result":"  1 | # GFF AI Platform: Phase 4 Secure Login, Client Portal & Admin Oversight Console\n  2 | \n  3 | This document establishes the strategic, enterprise-grade architecture, implementation details, and future backend contracts for **Phase 4** of the GFF AI Platform. \n  4 | \n  5 | In Phase 4, GFF AI delivers an advanced, premium, **high-fidelity presentation interface** representing the ultimate Sovereign Operating System for enterprise AI governance. This frontend is carefully designed with a zero-trust, decoupled aesthetic, ensuring that client-facing boards and internal GFF administrators can configure, simulate, and audit multi-agent system states with total security and confidence.\n  6 | \n  7 | ---\n  8 | \n  9 | ## 1. Executive Narrative & Visual Metaphor\n 10 | \n 11 | ### 1.1. The \"Air-Gapped Cockpit\"\n 12 | To provide boards of directors and enterprise security teams with absolute risk containment, the GFF AI Portal operates on an architecture metaphor of the **Air-Gapped Cockpit**. Just as a sophisticated flight simulator provides full-fidelity interactive controls, telemetry streams, and compliance feedback without endangering actual aircraft, the GFF AI Frontend presents a secure operational layer completely decoupled from live production model executors and database kernels.\n 13 | \n 14 | ### 1.2. Key Visual Metaphors Built Into Phase 4\n 15 | *   **The Zero-Trust Handshake**: Visual block diagrams showing AES-256 session token pathways keeping client model parameters invisible to presentation networks.\n 16 | *   **Decoupled Model Enclaves**: Isolated hypervisor-reinforced boxes representing hardware-level execution tracking protected by hardware seed security boundaries.\n 17 | *   **The Living Terminal Feed**: Live, simulated eBPF-level diagnostic event streams flowing within the login page and route-guard modal, reinforcing the premium, high-tech engineering nature of GFF AI's systems.\n 18 | *   **Role Negotiation Selector**: A highly custom bypass console allowing engineers to simulate and toggle between 7 distinct enterprise roles in real time, inspecting permission-based modules dynamically.\n 19 | \n 20 | ---\n 21 | \n 22 | ## 2. Implemented Routes & Navigation Map\n 23 | \n 24 | Phase 4 includes a fully realized, responsive, and secure routing matrix built using Next.js App Router. These public and protected paths are structured into distinct areas of operational clearance:\n 25 | \n 26 | ### 2.1. Authentication Routes (Public Preview / Entrypoints)\n 27 | *   `/login` — Central unified login terminal, defaulting to Client Portal entry.\n 28 | *   `/portal/login` — Explicit Client Portal gateway.\n 29 | *   `/admin/login` — Explicit GFF Administration gateway, defaulting to GFF Administrator credentials.\n 30 | \n 31 | ### 2.2. Client Portal Routes (`/portal/*`)\n 32 | The Client Portal is tailored for executive control, tactical project management, and cost-governance audits.\n 33 | *   `/portal/dashboard` — Unified Executive Control & Enclave Telemetry overview.\n 34 | *   `/portal/projects` — Milestone and sandbox pipeline overview.\n 35 | *   `/portal/projects/[id]` — Deep-dive tracker for an individual multi-agent project pipeline.\n 36 | *   `/portal/ai-operations` — Configurator for active agent profiles, model configurations, and memory parameters.\n 37 | *   `/portal/ai-operations/[id]` — Deep-dive sandbox editor for a specific cognitive pipeline.\n 38 | *   `/portal/control-center` — Sovereign control hub for hardware deployment and orchestrator clusters.\n 39 | *   `/portal/governance` — Live policy tracking and ISO compliance auditing.\n 40 | *   `/portal/documents` — Secure Sovereign legal vault and document index.\n 41 | *   `/portal/documents/[id]` — Inline document audit and validation engine.\n 42 | *   `/portal/billing` — Chronological \"Computational Epoch\" cost ledger and summaries.\n 43 | *   `/portal/billing/invoices` — List of current and past cryptographically signed invoices.\n 44 | *   `/portal/billing/invoices/[id]` — PDF-like interactive view of invoice ledgers.\n 45 | *   `/portal/analytics` — Dynamic resource, token, and memory lane analytics grids.\n 46 | *   `/portal/support` — SLA ticket pipeline and live wire connection.\n 47 | *   `/portal/support/[id]` — SLA wire communication log with active system engineers.\n 48 | *   `/portal/settings` — Client workspace profiles, API keys, and notification bounds.\n 49 | *   `/portal/activity` — Session tracking logs and cryptographic handshakes.\n 50 | \n 51 | ### 2.3. Admin Oversight Console Routes (`/admin/*`)\n 52 | The Admin Portal is tailored for GFF staff to manage client accounts, monitor global compute load, and handle system governance.\n 53 | *   `/admin/dashboard` — Oversight Deck with Global Telemetry, Enclave Status, and active incidents.\n 54 | *   `/admin/clients` — Master directory of all enterprise client accounts.\n 55 | *   `/admin/clients/[id]` — Dynamic client profile, active contracts, and allocated computational resources.\n 56 | *   `/admin/projects` — Global sandbox scheduler and execution milestone pipelines.\n 57 | *   `/admin/projects/[id]` — Master pipeline control room.\n 58 | *   `/admin/ai-operations` — Global model deployment, latency logs, and prompt-injection safety controls.\n 59 | *   `/admin/governance` — Master ISO compliance rules manager and guardrail template builder.\n 60 | *   `/admin/documents` — Master contract vault and blueprint compiler.\n 61 | *   `/admin/billing` — Accounts receivable ledger, contract terms manager, and computational SLA auditing.\n 62 | *   `/admin/analytics` — Global network traffic, queue latency, and multi-region cluster efficiency.\n 63 | *   `/admin/support` — Master ticket dispatcher, operator assignment, and SLA countdowns.\n 64 | *   `/admin/users` — GFF staff roster and IAM permissions management.\n 65 | *   `/admin/settings` — Global configuration, hardware regions, and emergency system boundaries.\n 66 | *   `/admin/activity` — Audit stream tracking all administrative overrides and credential rotations.\n 67 | \n 68 | ---\n 69 | \n 70 | ## 3. High-Fidelity Local Preview Auth Behavior\n 71 | \n 72 | To fulfill the \"frontend-only placeholder\" guardrails while delivering a deeply interactive premium experience, Phase 4 implements an innovative client-side authentication engine.\n 73 | \n 74 | ```\n 75 | +-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n 76 | |                            LOCAL PREVIEW AUTH ENGINE                              |\n 77 | |                                                                                   |\n 78 | |  1. Select Role Preset   -->   2. Auto-hydrate Mock Credentials                   |\n 79 | |  (Client Admin, etc.)          (Email, Cryptographic Salting logs)                |\n 80 | |                                                                                   |\n 81 | |  3. Trigger Handshake    -->   4. Simulate TLS Verification                       |\n 82 | |  (Password or OTP Auth)        (eBPF Terminal telemetry output animation)         |\n 83 | |                                                                                   |\n 84 | |  5. Store Session Key    -->   6. Redirect via Route Guard                        |\n 85 | |  (LocalStorage Cache)          (Enforces strict role permissions dynamically)     |\n 86 | +-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n 87 | ```\n 88 | \n 89 | ### 3.1. Credentials vs. One-Time Password (OTP) Dual-Mode Login\n 90 | The `/login` screen offers users a seamless mechanism to explore enterprise access models:\n 91 | 1.  **Credentials Mode**: Classic password input with built-in telemetry simulation. As the user types their password, simulated SHA-512 salting processes stream to the active console terminal.\n 92 | 2.  **MFA OTP Mode**: Simulates a rotating 6-digit One-Time Password. To mimic state-of-the-art enterprise multi-factor authentication, an automatic 30-second countdown cycle triggers the generation of new temporary tokens with simulated cryptographic rotation logs.\n 93 | \n 94 | ### 3.2. Animated Telemetry Terminal Console\n 95 | A live scrolling diagnostics feed is built directly into the login card. It streams low-noise, technical operation logs in real time, mirroring hardware-level eBPF system calls:\n 96 | *   `[INIT] Handshake request received from node terminal.`\n 97 | *   `[IDENTITY] Resolved profile context: client_admin`\n 98 | *   `[SSL/TLS] Session handshake initiated via SHA-256 cipher.`\n 99 | *   `[CRYPT] Salted passphrase vector: SHA-512_SALT_F38C...`\n100 | *   `[SANDBOX] Memory enclave isolated. Sandbox state: READY.`\n101 | \n102 | ---\n103 | \n104 | ## 4. Federated Identity & Access Management (IAM) Roles\n105 | \n106 | Phase 4 defines 7 discrete user identities across Client and Administrative boundaries, mapping directly to enterprise clearance levels.\n107 | \n108 | ### 4.1. Enterprise IAM Matrix\n109 | \n110 | | Role Key | Name | Clearance Level | Scope | Primary Responsibility |\n111 | | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n112 | | **`gff_admin`** | GFF Sovereign Superuser | `L-5 SYSTEM` | Global Admin & Portal | Total decentralized system override. Unfettered traversal of all client and admin enclaves. |\n113 | | **`gff_operator`** | GFF Systems Engineer | `L-4 OPERATIONAL` | Admin Console | Monitors physical infrastructure, active cluster health, queue latencies, and agent memory lanes. |\n114 | | **`finance_admin`**| GFF Financial Director | `L-3 FINANCE` | Admin & Client Billing | Oversees accounts receivable, billing tiers, epoch invoices, and SLA contract parameters. |\n115 | | **`support_agent`**| GFF Support Liaison | `L-3 SUPPORT` | Admin & Client Support | Dispatches and triage SLA tickets, maintains support channels, audits system logs. |\n116 | | **`client_admin`** | Client Administrator | `L-3 WORKSPACE` | Client Portal | Full control of client-owned sandboxes, project scopes, billing methods, and employee IAM. |\n117 | | **`client_member`**| Client Workspace Operator| `L-2 WORKSPACE` | Client Portal | Standard developer/user interface to deploy models, monitor telemetry, and view documents. |\n118 | | **`viewer`** | Global Compliance Auditor| `L-1 AUDIT` | Read-Only Views | Independent auditor node. Verifies compliance, ISO rule ledgers, and read-only activity logs. |\n119 | \n120 | ---\n121 | \n122 | ## 5. Security Route Guard Preview & Role Negotiation\n123 | \n124 | Protected paths are enclosed inside a client-side layout element (`PreviewRouteGuard.tsx`) which validates the cached session state from LocalStorage against the path's required permissions.\n125 | \n126 | ### 5.1. Dynamic Clearance Denial Overlay\n127 | When a user attempts to navigate to a section that exceeds their role's clearance level (e.g., a standard `client_member` attempting to view the Admin `/admin` suite, or a read-only `viewer` attempting to change `/portal/settings`), the route guard intercepts the render. Instead of a blank page or a raw 403 error, a premium **Clearance Violation Warning** is rendered inline:\n128 | *   **Security Alert Metrics**: Displays the user's current identity, clearance level, and the requested boundary.\n129 | *   **Interactive Counter-Sign**: Simulates a secure gateway query showing live network packets blocking traversal.\n130 | *   **Interactive Role Switcher**: A dropdown allowing users to instantly select a role with sufficient clearance, showcasing the route guard's live reactivity.\n131 | *   **Awaiting Override Countdown**: A 5-second animated gateway countdown that gracefully releases the lockout if an authorized override is simulated.\n132 | \n133 | ### 5.2. Granular Route-Access Logic\n134 | The authorization rules are codified inside `lib/preview-auth.ts`:\n135 | \n136 | ```typescript\n137 | // Client Portal clearance rules\n138 | export function canAccessPortalSection(role: PreviewRole, sectionId: string): boolean {\n139 |   if (role === \"gff_admin\") return true;\n140 |   if (role === \"viewer\") {\n141 |     return [\"dashboard\", \"analytics\", \"governance\", \"activity\"].includes(sectionId);\n142 |   }\n143 |   if (role === \"client_member\") {\n144 |     return ![\"billing\", \"settings\"].includes(sectionId);\n145 |   }\n146 |   if (role === \"client_admin\") return true;\n147 |   if (role === \"finance_admin\") {\n148 |     return [\"dashboard\", \"billing\", \"analytics\", \"activity\"].includes(sectionId);\n149 |   }\n150 |   if (role === \"support_agent\") {","success":true}],"durationMs":6}}
